content:
Set Up a Default No-Reply Email Address

Use an org-wide system email address to send your customers automated email about their cases. To include case details and customize your email template, create a verified custom No-Reply address.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To add an organization-wide address: Modify All Data

From Setup, enter Organization-Wide Addresses. Under Default No-Reply Address, click Add.
Enter a display name, your No-Reply email address, and select a purpose.

User Selection: Allow all users or designated profiles to choose this address as the From address when sending emails.
Default No-Reply Address: Case-related email notifications are sent from this address when Send Case Notifications from System Address is selected.
User Selection and Default No-Reply Address: All users can choose this address, also sending case-related notifications.

Click Save. An email is sent to verify your org's default No-Reply address. Verify it following the steps in the email.

Considerations:

* noreply@salesforce.com is used only when there isn't a default No-Reply email address set for your org.
* Six case-related scenarios trigger an email notification: assignment, comment, public comment, escalation, auto-assignment, and email on a case.
title: Set Up a Default No-Reply Email Address in Service Cloud
